ruleR44Expectation1Example.message:
A page where the CSS `transform` property has the `rotateZ` function conditionally applied on the orientation media feature - which does not restrict the element to either portrait or landscape orientation. 

```
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<title>Page with some content</title>
		<style>
			@media (orientation: portrait) {
				html {
					transform: rotateZ(1turn);
				}
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main>
			Page Content
		</main>
	</body>
```

ruleR62Expectation1Example.message:
This link, which is a different color from the surrounding text, uses a style similar to the default styling of links (underline) when it is focused or hovered.

```
<style>
	p {
		color: hsl(0, 50%, 25%);
		background-color: white;
	}
	a {
		text-decoration: none;
		color: hsl(232, 50%, 25%);
		background-color: white;
	}
	a:hover,
	a:focus {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}
</style>

```
<p>Read about WAI on the <a href="http://w3.org/WAI" target="_blank">WAI website</a>.</p>

ruleR62Expectation2Example.message:
This link uses a style similar to the default styling of links which underlines them in most browsers, making it a distinguishable style.

```
<style>
	p {
		color: hsl(0, 50%, 25%);
		background-color: white;
	}
	a {
		color: hsl(232, 50%, 25%);
		background-color: white;
		text-decoration: underline;
	}
</style>

ruleR73Expectation1Example.message:
Line height of 1.5 times font size, specified in a CSS style sheet.

```
p {
  line-height: 1.5;
}
```
Note that setting the line height in pixels (px), points (pt) or centimeters (cm) is possible but discouraged due to other accessibility concerns.

ruleR74Expectation1Example.message:
Font size using the relative length unit `em`. Inline CSS styling in an HTML document:

```
<p style="font-size:1.5em;">My text here</p>
```

Font size using the relative length measurement `%`, declared in a CSS stylesheet:

```
p {
  font-size: 150%;
}
```

